.657      1 Template:Infobox_Item\n 19.60%   25.981      1 Template:Soul_Wars\n 17.46%   23.141      1 Template:Dropping_monsters_list\n 13.85%   18.360      1 Template:Navbox\n 11.80%   15.638      1 Template:External\n  4.26%    5.650      1 Template:Ctg\n  3.99%    5.295      4 Template:Subject_changes\n  3.51%    4.649     15 Template:Plink\n  1.39%    1.836      4 Template:Chatl\n-->\n\n<!-- Saved in parser cache with key en_osrswiki:pcache:idhash:290880-0!canonical and timestamp 20220419210459 and revision id 14136529. Serialized with PHP.\n -->\n</div>","rawContent":"{{external|rs}}\n{{Infobox Item\n|defver = 2\n|version1 = Tutorial\n|version2 = In-match\n|name = Soul fragment\n|image = [[File:Soul fragment.png]]\n|release = [[6 January]] [[2021]]\n|update = Soul Wars And 20th Anniversary Event\n|members = Yes\n|quest = No\n|tradeable = No\n|bankable = No\n|placeholder = \n|equipable = No\n|stackable = Yes\n|noteable = \n|destroy1 = Nomad may be able to give you another.\n|destroy2 = You can obtain soul fragments by killing forgotten souls.\n|examine = Lightly pulsing with energy.\n|value = 1000\n|alchable = No\n|weight = 0.000\n|id1 = 25196\n|id2 = 25201\n}}\n[[File:Soul fragment detail.png|130px|left]]\n'''Soul fragments''' are obtained as drops from [[Forgotten Soul (Soul Wars)|Forgotten Soul]]s during a game of [[Soul Wars]]. They can also be obtained by killing players who possess them.\n\nThe fragments are used on the [[Soul Obelisk]] to reduce the damage reduction percentage of the [[Avatar of Creation]] and [[Avatar of Destruction|Destruction]]. The team who controls the Soul Obelisk will have each soul fragment reduce the Avatar's damage reduction percentage by one, while the team that does not have control will find that sacrificing soul fragments at the Soul Obelisk will only be worth one-third of the contribution.\n\n==Tutorial==\nIn the Soul Wars tutorial, players obtain one soul fragment as part of the demonstration. Attempting to pick up another from the ground will despawn the soul fragment from the ground, although players can cast [[Telekinetic Grab]] to obtain more.\n\nIf the player dies during the tutorial, the soul fragment is destroyed, and they must reclaim it from [[Nomad]] to continue progressing through the tutorial.\n\n==Drop sources==\n{{Dropping monsters list|Soul fragment}}\n\n==Changes==\n{{Subject changes header}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 20 January 2021\n|update = Puro-Puro Improvements and Barbarian Assault Changes\n|change = The tutorial's soul fragment value has been changed from 1 to 1,000.\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 13 January 2021\n|update = God Wars Instancing and Soul Wars Improvements\n|change = To make the in-match item appear above others when dropped, its value has been changed from 1 to 1,000. The tutorial's soul fragment value remained unchanged.\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 6 January 2021\n|update = Soul Wars And 20th Anniversary Event\n|change = The item is now obtainable by players.\n}}\n{{Subject changes\n|date = 9 December 2020\n|update = Christmas 2020\n|change = The item was added to the game.\n}}\n{{Subject changes footer}}\n\n{{Soul Wars}}"}